    "body": "## Scope\n\nRealign the Boomer Step 4.4B aggregate acceptance contract after user Safari proved that all four remaining failures are stale/incomplete child-smoke checks rather than demonstrated product regressions.\n\nExact base: `120feb63e7a4def269a46c7e53b19ba9b19181da`.\n\nThe two immediately preceding `main` commits (`77dfbf5...`, `120feb63...`) are an already-disclosed integration-control incident that created and then removed an empty `__noop__`; compare from pre-incident main has zero net file delta. This PR is isolated from that incident and starts from current main.\n\nChanged paths only:\n- `AsyncScene/Web/dev/boomer-step4-4b-current-contract-adapter.js`\n- `docs/dev/boomer-step4-4b-current-contract-adapter.js`\n- `AsyncScene/Web/index.html`\n- `docs/index.html`\n\nAdapter mirrors are byte-identical at Git blob `d3171700617470b39dbd851bf1ec4d5d22985cee`.\nIndex mirrors are byte-identical at Git blob `f484e9a58df452e8d3de04503ce2a0f5c8b1baf7`; each index changes by exactly one added script tag.\n\n## Safari evidence\n\nAfter PR #253:\n- expected scope-recovery asset loaded;\n- no recent runtime errors;\n- `addUnique`, base-smoke alias, Boomer 4.4B, Boomer profile-diff, Zoomer Fix4, and Zoomer UI/NPC-length alias were all functions;\n- Fix5 executed completely without a thrown exception;\n- all state/profile/economy/battle/moneyLog/persistence/localStorage restoration booleans were true;\n- all six adversarial restoration fixtures were true;\n- only four checks failed: `base_smoke`, `profile_diff`, `placeholders`, `emoji_contracts`.\n\n## Why those four checks are stale\n\n1. `base_smoke`: legacy Step 3.5 expects old corpus counts/hashes (126/128/290), while current runtime reports 131/133/295 with zero unresolved runtime gaps and clean alias/mapping/variable invariants.\n2. `profile_diff`: the June-17 smoke requires that no standalone Boomer profile and no `Data.TEXTS.boomer` exist. Current accepted Stage 6 architecture intentionally uses Boomer profile dictionaries.\n3. `placeholders`: legacy aggregate treats every `{[A-Z0-9_]+}` token as suspicious, but current accepted contract explicitly contains legitimate `{X}` and the current 4.4A audit passes placeholder integrity.\n4. `emoji_contracts`: legacy aggregate scans only TEXTS/START/NPC/COP, omitting accepted emoji-bearing `CAP_MESSAGES` and DOM surfaces.\n\nCurrent authoritative 4.4A audit remains `STATIC_PASS / READY_FOR_RUNTIME_SMOKE`, 147/147 PASS, fail 0, structural 0.\n\n## Repair\n\nAdd a post-dev-check adapter that:\n- preserves the raw Fix5 smoke as `smokeBoomerEconomyConflictTerminologyLegacyRawOnce`;\n- supersedes only the four proven-stale checks;\n- synchronously validates the deployed current 4.4A audit markers/counts and placeholder authority;\n- validates the current standalone Boomer profile architecture;\n- validates 💰/⭐/⚡ across current data, `CAP_MESSAGES`, and live DOM icons;\n- retains meaningful legacy Step 3.5 runtime-health invariants such as zero unresolved gaps, no runtime logic touch, no stale body, clean alias/mapping/variable mismatch arrays, and required artifact existence;\n- preserves all other raw runtime checks fail-closed;\n- still requires all restoration booleans, all six adversarial fixtures, and the loaded-runtime-asset identity contract.\n\nNo product copy, gameplay, economy, battle, NPC, state, persistence, or existing `dev-checks.js` source is changed.\n\nSafari acceptance remains `PENDING_USER` until post-merge rerun.",
